## Notes
- The Peacekeeper (a guard NPC) intervenes and attacks the player if you fight beastly fido/odif yltsaeb near town squares — got hit hard (lost ~8 HP in one hit) and had to flee east through the city gate. Fight these mobs somewhere the Peacekeeper isn't watching, or expect to flee.
- **PEACEKEEPER COMBAT ASSESSMENT**: Two direct attack attempts at level 3 have failed. Peacekeeper hits extremely hard (~6 HP per thrash), dagger damage is minimal. Need to be level 5-6+ with better weapons (not dagger) to have a realistic chance. Strategy: Level up to 5-6, acquire a better sword/mace, then attempt.
- East of the east gate ("City Entrance" and beyond) is flagged "above your recommended level" — avoid until higher level.
- Guild entrances (Thieves' Guild bar, Clerics' Guild bar) are blocked by guards for non-members.
- Weapon shop buys weapons (sold small sword for 23g here) — useful for offloading loot, but remember to also buy a replacement weapon.
